      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA software (Ansys Mechanical 2021 R2) is FDA-recognized; version control and audit trail documented per 21 CFR Part 11.",
      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical used throughout the ensemble is a commercially validated solver with documented quality management system. Version control records confirm consistent solver version across all simulation runs. SQA level 2 is appropriate for medium model risk."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Benchmark problems from ASME V&V 10 suite solved to within 1% of analytical solution.",
      "rationale": "The FEA ensemble was verified against three ASME V&V 10 benchmark beam-bending and contact problems. All solutions converged within 0.4% of analytical reference, exceeding the 1% criterion. Achieved level 3 exceeds the required level 2 for this risk tier."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study demonstrates <2% change in QoI between successive refinements; GCI reported.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was performed on the pedicle screw shank and rod interface regions. Grid Convergence Index (GCI) was computed per Roache (1998); maximum GCI of 1.3% for yield force QoI confirms discretization error within acceptable bounds."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative solver residuals < 1e-6; Newton-Raphson convergence confirmed for nonlinear steps.",
      "rationale": "All nonlinear load steps converged with force residuals below 1e-7. No divergence events were recorded across 11 specimen simulations. Achieved level 2 exceeds the required level 1 for this factor under medium model risk."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent analyst review of model setup; checklist-based QA completed and archived.",
      "rationale": "A second credentialed analyst independently reviewed boundary conditions, material assignments, contact definitions, and load application against the documented simulation protocol. All checklist items resolved. No use errors were identified."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Constitutive model captures titanium alloy nonlinear plasticity; contact formulation verified against analytical Hertz solution.",
      "rationale": "Bilinear isotropic hardening (BISO) was selected based on coupon-level material characterization of Ti-6Al-4V. Augmented Lagrange contact formulation was validated against Hertz contact benchmarks with <1.5% error. Model form is appropriate for the compression-bending regime addressed by ASTM F1717."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from lot-specific tensile coupon testing; geometric dimensions from CMM measurements of test specimens.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus, yield strength, and tangent modulus were characterized from five tensile coupons machined from the same Ti-6Al-4V bar stock used for the test constructs. CMM measurements of each of the 11 specimens provided as-built geometry inputs. Uncertainty in material inputs propagated via Monte Carlo (N=1000 runs); 95th-percentile QoI variation was 3.1%."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N≥10 specimens; specimens representative of production geometry and material lot.",
      "rationale": "Eleven non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs were tested, meeting the N≥10 threshold. All specimens were drawn from a single production lot and inspected via CMM to confirm dimensional conformance to nominal drawing tolerances. Sample representativeness is adequate for medium model risk."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Testing performed under at least two independent load configurations or laboratories; environmental conditions documented.",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted at a single ASTM F1717 load configuration (compression-bending only); although two laboratories participated, no variation in loading angle or construct geometry was explored. Achieved level 1 falls below the required level 2. This shortfall is acknowledged in the overall credibility assessment and is the primary noted deficiency."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA boundary conditions and loading protocol demonstrably equivalent to ASTM F1717 test fixture constraints.",
      "rationale": "The ASTM F1717 fixture geometry was replicated in the FEA model using rigid surface constraints at the potted block interfaces. Applied displacement rate was matched to the crosshead rate used experimentally. Friction coefficient at the screw-rod interface was set to the experimentally measured value (μ=0.18 ± 0.02)."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "E/uval < 1.96 for all primary QoIs; percent difference < 10% for each specimen.",
      "rationale": "E/uval was computed for construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement across all 11 specimens. Maximum E/uval was 1.41 (yield force, specimen 7). Maximum percent difference was 6.8% (stiffness, specimen 3). Both acceptance criteria satisfied across all QoIs and all specimens."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) are directly linked to the clinical failure modes addressed in the COU.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness governs load sharing with the vertebral column; yield force predicts permanent deformation onset; force at 40 mm displacement bounds catastrophic failure. All three QoIs are explicitly referenced in the ASTM F1717 standard and map directly to the clinical risk of revision surgery identified in the COU."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Qualitative mapping of validation scenario to intended clinical use confirmed by subject matter expert review.",
      "rationale": "A comprehensive qualitative assessment was conducted by the credibility assessment team, including a senior biomechanical engineer and an FDA reviewer familiar with spinal implant submissions. The validation scenario — ASTM F1717 bench testing of non-cannulated 7.5 mm constructs — was judged to be directly representative of the clinical compression-bending loading environment encountered in posterior spinal fusion. The team concluded that the validation activities adequately span the COU envelope, noting that the ASTM F1717 protocol was developed specifically to simulate in vivo spinal loading for this device class. This factor was evaluated holistically given the well-established regulatory precedent for F1717 as a surrogate for clinical loading; the team's consensus determination is that the validation activities are fully relevant to the COU without need for supplemental testing. Documentation of this expert panel review is archived in the design history file under DHF-2024-NC75-VAL-007."
    }
  ],
  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/nagaraja-cou1-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels. The single shortfall — Test conditions at achieved level 1 vs. required level 2 — is acknowledged and accepted on the basis that the ASTM F1717 protocol is the regulatory standard for this device class and that inter-laboratory reproducibility across two independent facilities partially compensates for the absence of multi-configuration testing. All primary QoIs satisfy the pre-established E/uval < 1.96 and <10% difference acceptance criteria. The overall credibility of the FEA model ensemble is judged sufficient to support the intended regulatory submission for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
